content:
Transfer dashboard ownership if responsibilities change or the current dashboard owner leaves your organization. The new owner has full control over the dashboard contents.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

User permissions needed:
- View All Data to change the dashboard owner to anyone in your org
- Manage My Team’s Dashboards to change the dashboard owner from and to anyone who rolls up to you in your team’s Role Hierarchy
- Edit My Dashboards, Create Customize Dashboards, Manage Dashboards, Manage Dynamic Dashboards (for dynamic dashboards), and View My Team's Dashboards (for Dynamic Dashboards with Run As Selected User specified) to be assigned as the owner of a dashboard

To change ownership:
On the Analytics tab or the Dashboards tab, find the dashboard. Select | Change Owner. Select the new owner. To send an email notification to the new owner, select Send Email Notification. Click Submit.

You can also change ownership of multiple dashboards by selecting them on the Analytics tab and clicking Manage Items | Change Owner.
title: Changing Dashboard Ownership in Salesforce Analytics
